# Jekyll Plugins

- The docs build with Jekyll + Liquid. Do not use Hugo shortcode syntax (`{{< ... >}}`, `{{% ... %}}`).
- Allowed plugins from project configs:
  - `jekyll-regex-replace`;
  - `jekyll_include_plugin`;
  - `jekyll_asset_pipeline`.
- In fenced code blocks, language identifier is mandatory and must be listed in `.cursor/rules/docs/hugo-supported-codeblock-languages.mdc`.

## Allowed Liquid Tags In Markdown

- `alert` block (custom plugin in `_plugins/alert.rb`):
  - use `{% alert %}...{% endalert %}`;
  - optional `level` values used in docs: `info`, `warning`, `danger`;
  - if level is omitted, default is `info`.
- `offtopic` block (custom plugin in `_plugins/offtopic.rb`, used for collapsible details):
  - use `{% offtopic title="..." %}...{% endofftopic %}`.
- `include`:
  - use `{% include path/to/file.liquid %}` or include Markdown partials.
  - if `include` is used for documentation pages, the included file must be located in `docs/documentation/_includes/`.
- `raw`:
  - wrap Liquid/Go-template examples with `{% raw %}...{% endraw %}` so they are shown as text.
- Standard Liquid control flow and variables are allowed:
  - `{% if %}`, `{% endif %}`, `{% capture %}`, `{{ site.* }}`, `{{ page.* }}`, and filters (for example `| regex_replace`).

## Examples

```go-html-template
{% alert level="warning" %}
Warning message.
{% endalert %}
```

```go-html-template
{% offtopic title="Example output..." %}
`d8 k get pods -A`
{% endofftopic %}
```

```go-html-template
{% include admin/integrations/openstack-based-configuration.md %}
```

```go-html-template
{% raw %}
{{ include "helm_lib_module_image" (list . "helloworld") }}
{% endraw %}
```

## Prohibited Patterns

- Do not use Hugo shortcodes (`{{< alert >}}`, `{{< tabs >}}`, `{{% details %}}`).
- Do not invent non-existent Jekyll tags; use only tags implemented in project plugins or standard Liquid tags.
